OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F418A1778429470
OL,3,CFive party contests see Conservatives
OL,4,Cand Labour lose grip on southern
OL,5,Ccouncils
OL,7,FVoters have dramatically drawn to an
OL,8,Fend decades of dominance by the
OL,9,FConservatives on county councils in
OL,10,Fthe South and South East.
OL,12,FTories majorities tumbled at county
OL,13,Fhalls in Hampshire and West Sussex,
OL,14,Fwhere the party has enjoyed outright
OL,15,Fcontrol since 1997.
OL,17,FIn East Sussex, the Conservatives
OL,18,Fcollapsed to fourth place, despite
OL,19,Frunning a minority administration
OL,20,Fprior to polling day.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G1/9
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
